servings: 2
---

Pour @water{240%ml} (double for 4p) into a large #pot, stir in the @vegetable stock{1%sachet} and bring to the boil.

Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%grams}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}.

Pop a #lid on the pot and remove from the heat.

Leave aside for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips, then chop into roughly 1cm pieces.

Place a #pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Add the @diced Irish chicken breast{260%grams} and pepper. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Fry until chicken is cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add @Middle Eastern style spice mix{1%sachet}. Cook for ~{1%minute}.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is due to packaging used to keep it fresh.

Meanwhile, trim the @baby gem{120%grams}, halve lengthways and thinly slice widthways.

In a large #bowl, combine the @aioli{2%sachets}, @paprika{1%sachet}, @honey{1%sachet} and @sugar{1/2%tsp} (double for 4p).

Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Reserve 1 tbsp of dressing per person for drizzling over the salad before serving.

When everything is ready, add the chicken, pepper, salad leaves and bulgur to the bowl with the dressing.

Carefully toss until everything is well combined and coated in the dressing.

Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Share the chicken and bulgur salad between bowls.

Drizzle with the reserved dressing.

Finish with a crumble of @Greek style cheese{100%grams}.